\f0\fs24 She took a moment to come up with a plan. In the past, she\'92d had success with home invasions by making her way around to the back of a house and entering via the servant\'92s entrance, or an open window, or even, on one occasion, a wine cellar. But the side of the house was blocked by Connor\'92s elaborate garden, which sprawled across his lawn on either side of the front walkway. Annabel didn\'92t fancy treading through rose bushes to get around the side of the house. There had to be an easier way. Perhaps, she thought, a head-on approach would be best. She decided to use the front entrance.
