\f0\fs24 \cf0 \'93Thank you, Captain Merrick,\'94 he said, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivcmt://28CFAAF9-6F78-4853-A98C-4BA09998B346"}}{\fldrslt loud as he could manage. He knew he was being obnoxious}}, but it wouldn't be the first time Jonathan had made a scene at a party.
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 He returned his hat to his head and joined the lineup, while those who had been staring at him the whole time turned away and resumed their conversations as if to give the impression that they\'92d hardly noticed him. He \ul flashed a cocky grin at the woman in front of him\ulnone , while she hastily drew out a fan in order to give the impression that her attention had been fixed on the unseasonable warmth of the weather this evening and not on him. She blushed.
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 \'93Mr. Grimmer, I presume?\'94 she said, indicating the company name emblazoned on the airship beneath the ship\'92s own name. 
\i Grimmer and Sons Publishing Inc.
\f1\i0\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 \'93Mr. Grimmer was my father,\'94 Jonathan told her, trying not to let it show that she\'92d just thrust a dagger in his heart. She couldn\'92t have known that the mere mention of his family name was painful. Mr. Grimmer had died recently\'97a tragic hunting accident. It had been less than a week since Jonathan heard the news.
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 The young lady gave him a smile.
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 \'93It must be a family business, then?\'94 she asked. She curtseyed, and added, \'93I\'92m Lucy Marshall, by the way.\'94
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 \'93Charmed,\'94 said Jonathan, flashing a smile. Miss Marshall\'92s fan fluttered in response. \'93And yes, you\'92re quite right. Family business, although the name is a bit misleading. My father insisted on calling it 
\i Grimmer and Sons
\i0 , although I\'92m an only child.\'94
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 Miss Marshall\'92s male companion turned around to join the conversation, a look of impatience on his face. The man {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivcmt://6680C19A-F082-419C-952A-5C070C446DCF"}}{\fldrslt wore}} arched eyebrows and had an aquiline nose. He {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivcmt://E02B3017-638C-4F29-A161-DBB9F0FFD058"}}{\fldrslt wore}} a sneer on his lip.
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 \'93{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivcmt://147D79D6-A13C-454B-B59F-801DD5F9BCD2"}}{\fldrslt Solomon Grundy}},\'94 he said, tipping his hat and offering a forced smile. He placed his hand on Miss Marshall\'92s arm, puffing out his chest.
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 Jonathan snorted. \'93{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivcmt://789BDFB6-FAB9-4789-A508-F14276E3BE45"}}{\fldrslt An unfortunate name}},\'94 he said impulsively, then instantly regretted it as Grundy\'92s eyebrows narrowed impossibly further.
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 As they spoke, a young gentleman bumped into Jonathan. The man asked their pardon as he barged his way through the line. They parted, letting him by, none of them quite sure how else to proceed.
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 \'93Well, that was rude,\'94 said Grundy. \'93Anyway, I understand the Grimmer Company runs a number of newspapers and literary magazines, isn't that right? Quite a business, I imagine.\'94
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 \'93We also publish penny dreadfuls,\'94 Jonathan said with a grin, enjoying the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivcmt://71FE4DBF-F219-41B8-A1BC-AE2D60244643"}}{\fldrslt look}} on Grundy's face. Meanwhile, Miss Marshall\'92s eyes lit up.
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 The sensationalism and bloody subject matter of penny bloods were not considered to be in good taste among proper gentlemen. Jonathan was a man accustomed to the comforts of the wealthiest families in London, but he was still just a newspaper man\'97n, not exactly a respectable career among the ton. He enjoyed shocking more respectable gentlemen by talking about the source of his family\'92s wealth.
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 \'93\'93{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivcmt://D8CA723A-AE0A-43E2-A1C2-750AEB86EFFE"}}{\fldrslt Actually, I\'92ve only just returned to London; I\'92d been away, traveling, but have been summoned back to take over the business. .\'94}} In fact, Jonathan had only come back to England upon hearing the news of his father\'92s death. \'93I thought I\'92d start by writing an article for one of the company\'92s journals.\'94
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 He disengaged his attention for a moment to peer ahead at the progress of the line. It was moving along quickly, Lord Connor\'92s servants competently ushering the guests inside. Jonathan would have hated to be stuck making small talk for long. He had enough on his mind as it was.
\f1\fs20 \
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivcmt://AD7EE898-E9CD-4FA0-9189-D333E8689273"}}{\fldrslt 
\f0\fs24 \'93Mr. Grimmer? May I ask what it is that you\'92re writing?\'94}}\

\f0\fs24 \'93Sorry,\'94 he said, returning his attention to the conversation. \'93\'93Actually, I\'92m afraid I have an ulterior motive in attending this ball. I\'92m writing an article about Lord Connor.\'94
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 \'93Oh, really? On what subject?\'94 asked Grundy. \'93I\'92ve known Lord Connor a long time. Perhaps I could be useful.\'94
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 Jonathan hesitated. He wanted to hear from Connor before saying anything more on the subjectmatter. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivcmt://2AA6385E-1ED1-4B0C-AC96-B3FD9C051D33"}}{\fldrslt In fact}}, this was the first time he\'92d told anyone that he was writing about Connor. He thrust a hand into his pocket and felt a small scrap of paper in his father\'92s handwriting.
\f1\fs20 \
