\f0\fs24 As the dance ended, they showed their appreciation for the musicians by joining in the applause, which all but drowned out the sound of a muffled gunshot from upstairs. }}
\f0\fs24 It was a sound that Jonathan had heard before; his father had been a hunter. Otherwise, he might not even have noticed it. His eyes darted upwards, but when he returned his attention to Lucy, it seemed that he was alone in having heard it.
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 \'93What is it?\'94 she asked, having noticed that Jonathan\'92s attention had wandered.
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 \'93Did you hear that?\'94
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 \'93Hear what?\'94 she replied.
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 Jonathan shook his head, second-guessing himself. Perhaps it was just the clang of clockwork, a {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivcmt://D2DF1273-2425-4D25-AD3F-711FF0D7D6AD"}}{\fldrslt cog in the machine that rotated the ballroom}}.
