\f0\fs24 Miss Marshall paused to think for a moment.
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 \'93Lord Connor\'92s study, I believe,\'94 she replied, \'93Why? What is it that you heard?\'94
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 \'93Thank you, Miss Marshall,\'94 said Jonathan. \'93Be sure to give my regards to Mr. Grundy.\'94
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 Any other night, Jonathan would have been happy to remain in Miss Marshall\'92s company{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivcmt://1347F16C-61A6-4BE0-B416-E104E6BAC1E5"}}{\fldrslt . He might have made a contest of it, }}to see if he could steal her right from under Grundy\'92s nose. Tonight, he had other things on his mind. He beelined for the stairway, which he was relieved to see was crowded with other guests. It seemed there was a balcony upstairs, which was populated by gentlemen who had the good grace to take their cigarettes outside.
\f1\fs20 \

