\f0\fs24 Just because Connor was dead didn\'92t mean he couldn\'92t still be robbed. She spared her new accomplice one last glance. She wondered if she could trust him not to run off as soon as her back was turned.
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 She}}
\f0\fs24  turned away and made her way over to the safe. This would be much more difficult now that she could no longer demand the safe\'92s combination from its owner. But she set to work cracking it.
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 \'93There was something wrong with him. He was sick,\'94 she said, as she fiddled with the lock.
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 \'93Hm?\'94 said Mr. O, who was standing at the door, true to his word.
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 \'93Lord Connor. I didn\'92t come here to kill him. He was sick. Deranged. He came at me. I had to put him down. I was merely defending myself.\'94
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 She put a hand to her lips. She needed to listen for the click of the lock as she slowly turned it. Then it clicked. She made a mental note of the number, then began to turn the dial the opposite way.
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 \'93Sick how?\'94 Mr. O asked. \'93Consumption? Ergotism?\'94
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 Annabel looked up from her work. \'93Something else, I think. He was trying to eat me,\'94 she offered by way of example.
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 \'93He 
\i what
\i0 ?\'94 Mr. O exclaimed.
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 \'93Well, look at him. He\'92s far too rotten given he\'92s only been dead a few minutes. Clearly there was something wrong with him. Anyway, this really isn\'92t the time. Is anyone coming? This is taking longer than I\'92d hoped.\'94
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 \'93Still clear,\'94 he said.
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 Annabel had to remind herself to breathe. It was easy to get lost in her work. That was why she wanted a lookout. She couldn\'92t afford to be listening for approaching footsteps when she was intent on hearing the click of the mechanical components of the lock. She needed only one more number, and she nearly had it.
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 \'93I think someone\'92s coming,\'94 Mr. O said suddenly.
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 \'93Almost\'85\'94 she said, ignoring him. She really was almost there, if she could just get that one last number. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivcmt://B3B1FF68-ABF4-4D57-902C-30FF40C68D60"}}{\fldrslt She continued to work the lock, listening for the tell-tale sound of the lock sliding into place.}}
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 \'93We\'92ve got to go,\'94 he whispered urgently.
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 Cursing, she looked up from her work. Mr. O had shut the door and had his ear pressed against it, listening for the approaching footsteps of whoever was coming. She watched in silence, holding her breath as Mr. O tensed.
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 A minute passed in silence as they waited for the door to burst open on them. Again, she drew her Derringer. She aimed it at the doorway, even as she willed the door not to open. So far, this had gone exactly how she 
\i didn\'92t
\i0  want it to go. She began to ask if the coast was clear, but Mr. O shushed her.
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 Another minute passed. She could hear floorboards creaking outside the door, even over the sound of the music from downstairs. Finally, Mr. O took a deep breath and turned back to her, relief clearly written on his face.
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 \'93False alarm, I suppose,\'94 he said. \'93They must have gone into the other room. Still, someone is bound to have noticed Connor\'92s absence by now. We can\'92t afford to linger any longer than we already have.\'94
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 Annabel agreed.agreedhad to agree. Still, she wasn\'92t leaving until she had what she\'92d come here for. She didn\'92t bother saying so aloud; she simply returned her attention to cracking the safe. Annabel swiveled the dial, more quickly now. At last, it slid into the correct position. She heard the satisfying click announcing that she\'92d gotten it. {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivcmt://0808A3D5-5483-4FAB-9806-67F1E583B50D"}}{\fldrslt To the untrained ear, the sound would have been easily missed, but Annabel was an expert.}} \'93Got it.\'94
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 She pulled the door open and hastily withdrew a thick, yellow envelope. She got to her feet and {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivcmt://2D7871FC-51CA-4D08-92C5-FF2845BBB21D"}}{\fldrslt stealthily}} made her way to Mr. O. She realized she was grinning, and she felt that flush of excitement she always felt when she\'92d 
\i retrieved 
\i0 an item of value. O was looking at her impatiently, {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivcmt://31B49BC6-B349-4C0F-9CAF-4D287D54178C"}}{\fldrslt but she couldn\'92t help but notice how blue his eyes were. A woman could get lost in those eyes.}}
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 Smiling as she handled the envelope from Connor\'92s safe, she forced herself to focus.
\f1\fs20 \

\f0\fs24 \'93So, how do we get out of here?\'94
\f1\fs20 \
{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "scrivcmt://6ADE68D8-8BD8-470E-BD60-111287700C23"}}{\fldrslt 
\f0\fs24 He held up a finger\'97a, as if to say 
